  "texts": [
    "Sampling from the trained model requires integrating the learned field over time:",
    "typically using numerical ODE solvers such as Euler's method.",
    "Although the true OT vector field is constant, the learned approximation typically is not, and integration quality still depends on the time discretization.",
    "We provide a detailed description of the datasets used and generated, as well as the method employed to compute residuals during training.",
    "We use the dataset introduced by Bastek (2024) to enable direct comparison with their results."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}